.TH VOLS 1 "March 2026" "bas-cpp" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vols \- list local volumes detected by bas-cpp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vols
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vols
enumerates local volumes known to the bas-cpp volume subsystem and prints
one header row plus one line per volume. Columns are tab-separated.
.PP
If you do not pass any field-selection option
.RB ( \-a ", " \-c ", " \-m ", " \-d ", " \-t ", " \-l ", " \-u ", " \-r ", " \-L ", " \-D ", " \-o ", " \-O ", " \-z ),
the default columns are
.BR \-mdtlu
(mount point, device, type, label, UUID).
With
.BR \-v " / " \-\-verbose ,
the default columns are
.BR \-mdtlurLD
(those five plus read-only, logical type, loop device).
.B \-c " / " \-\-compact
selects only the compact column set
.RB ( \-mdtlu ),
even with
.BR \-v .
.B \-a " / " \-\-all
selects every column (same as combining all field flags).
.PP
Bind mounts are always included in the scan.
Overlay filesystems are added when you pass
.BR \-s " / " \-\-symbols ,
or when the logical-type column is selected
.RB ( \-L " / " \-\-logical-type ,
or
.B \-v
defaults).
.PP
.B \-w " / " \-\-writable
lists only writable mounts and implies the read-only column
.RB ( \-r )
so each printed row still shows
.BR ro " / " rw .
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Field columns
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Print every available column.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-compact
Use the compact column set
.RB ( \-mdtlu );
with explicit field flags, compact is ORed with those columns.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mountpoint
Mount point (or root path).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-device
Device path (or \-).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-type
Volume type.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-label
Label.
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-uuid
UUID.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-read-only
Read-only flag (\fBro\fR / \fBrw\fR).
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-logical-type
Logical mount kind (\fB\-\fR, \fBbind\fR, \fBoverlay\fR).
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-loop-device
Loop device marker (\fBloop\fR / \fB\-\fR).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-opts
Per-mount (VFS) option string from
.BR /proc/self/mountinfo .
.TP
.BR \-O ", " \-\-superopts
Superblock option string from
.BR /proc/self/mountinfo .
.TP
.BR \-z ", " \-\-root
Root path within the filesystem (mountinfo \(lqroot\(rq field, before the mount point).
.SS Other
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-symbols
Include overlay filesystems in the volume scan (bind mounts are always included).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage and exit successfully.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-writable
Omit read-only volumes; implies
.BR \-r .
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Lower the library log threshold (more messages on stderr). With no field flags, selects the verbose default column set.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress library warnings on stderr (errors only).
.PP
.B \-v
and
.B \-q
cannot be used together.
.B \-a
and
.B \-c
cannot be used together.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Exits 0 on success, 2 for invalid options, conflicting flags, or unexpected arguments.
.SH AUTHORS
Written as part of the bas-cpp project.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bas-cpp (7)
